<h1>Disk File</h1>
<p>
To specify which .ide file to use click the 'IDE' button (highlighted in yellow) or type in a specific ide filename (highlighted in orange). Default 'elf2k.ide' is used but this can be changed to any file name. Number of tracks, heads and sectors can be specified via the <a href="ElfPorts.htm">Device Port</a> button, default is 512 tracks, 4 heads and 26 sectors. ElfOs can be installed on the ide disk file, see also <a href="Elf2KElfOs.htm">Installation Elf/Os 2.8</a> or <a href="Elf2KElfOs_3.0.htm">Installation Elf/Os 3.0</a>. The eject button (highlighted in purple) will empty the ide filename field (highlighted in orange).
</p>
<p>
<IMG SRC="images/elf2000_disk.png" BORDER="0">
</p>
<p>
After initial start-up the file elf2k-installation.ide is made available including a pre installed Elf/Os and additional Elf/Os software. The installation file will be renamed to elf2k.ide if that file doesn't exist.
</p>
</BODY>
